==English==
===Etymology===
From Latin ''[[di-#Latin|di-]]'', from ''[[dis-#Latin|dis-]]'', "apart", + ''[[vergere]]'', "to bend".

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɜː(r)dʒ|-ɜː(r)dʒ]]

===Verb===
'''to diverge'''
# ''(intransitive)'' to [[run]] [[apart]]; to [[tend]] into [[different]] [[direction]]s
# ''(intransitive)'' (''mathematics'') (of a sequence) to have no [[limit]]
====Antonyms====
*to [[converge]] (1,2)
====Translations====
*German: [[divergieren]] (1,2)
*[[Ido]]: [[divergar]]
